{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|おお}}

{{IPAchar|/opo/}} → {{IPAchar|/ofo/}} → {{IPAchar|/oho/}} → {{IPAchar|/oː/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=おお|-}}.

Cognate with {{m|ja|大|tr=ō||[[great]], [[large]]}}, and the ''oho-'' element in {{ja-r|おほほし||unclear, indistinct; depressed, gloomy; stupid, imbecilic}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

Historically also realized as ''obo'' in old texts, and cognate with the ''obo-'' element in {{m|ja|朧||tr=oboro|hazy, vague, dim, indistinct}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

